<div class="default-page">
    <div class="header">
        <h1 id="main-title" class="container"><%= __('CoinRaiser') %></h1>
        <h3 class="container">Bitcoin fundraising made easy!</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="main container clearfix">
        <h1>CoinRaiser Tutorial</h1>
        <p>Everything you need to know to get familiar with the CoinRaiser bitcoin fundraising platform.</p>
        <ul class="getting-started">
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>Create CoinRaiser User</h3>
                    <p>
                        Create your CoinRaiser account by tapping the <strong>Sign Up</strong> button. Simply provide a username, email address, and password. This is all you need to create fundraising campaigns and make donation pledges to campaigns.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>Login to CoinRaiser</h3>
                    <p>
                        If you already have a CoinRaiser account, login to the CoinRaiser app by tapping the <strong>Log In</strong> button. Simply provide your username and password.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>
                        Connect with CoinBase
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        In order to collect funds from your fundraising campaigns or to donate funds to campaigns, you must connect with your Coinbase account. If you do not have a Coinbase account, <a target="_blank" href="https://coinbase.com/?r=531eb4328b0a0d164c0002c6&utm_campaign=user-referral&src=referral-link">tap here to sign up</a>. By signing up through this link, you are helping support CoinRaiser. <strong>You will receive $5 in bitcoin at no cost to you</strong> once you fund your account with at least $100. Your support is very much appreciated!
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        To connect with Coinbase, tap the <strong>Connect with Coinbase</strong> button. Enter your Coinbase username and password and tap the <strong>Sign In</strong> button. Then tap the <strong>Authorize</strong> button to give CoinRaiser permission to send and receive funds on your behalf.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>
                        Browse Campaigns
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Tap the <strong>All Campaigns</strong> tab to view available campaigns. Swipe up and down through the list to scroll. When you find a campaign you'd like to contribute to, tap on it to view full campaign details.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>
                        Create Campaign
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        Tap the <strong>My Campaigns</strong> tab to view your campaigns and create a new campaign. Tap on the <strong>Launch New Campaign</strong> button and provide a campaign name, description, funding goal, and images. When you launch the campaign, all CoinRaiser users will be able to see it and donate to your cause. If you are not linked to a Coinbase account, donated funds will stored at Coinbase in an escrow account managed by CoinRaiser. Once you connect to Coinbase, you will be able to immediately claim 100% of the donations and they will be sent to your personal Coinbase account. All donations are sent directly to your Coinbase account without going to escrow if you are already a linked Coinbase user when you create your campaign.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>
                        Pledge to Campaign
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        A pledge allows users who do not yet have Coinbase account to create a promise to help out a campaign. Once you have created a Coinbase account, funded it with bitcoin, and connected it to CoinRaiser, you will be able to fulfill your pledge.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        When you find a campaigns you wish to participate in, tap the <strong>Donate</strong> button. Enter the amount of mBTC (milli-bitcoins) you would like to pledge. One bitcoin is the same as 1000 mBTC. The current market rate in US dollars of your pledge is shown. If you are not linked to a Coinbase account, your donation will be created as a pledge that you can fulfill once you have connected to a funded Coinbase account. If you are already connected to Coinbase, then your donation will be immediately funded from the bitcoin in your Coinbase account.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>
                        Donate to Campaign
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                        A donation is an immediate transfer of funds from your Coinbase account to a campaign. This happens only if your Coinbase account is connected to CoinRaiser and you have the funds available.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        When you find a campaigns you wish to participate in, tap the <strong>Donate</strong> button. Enter the amount of mBTC (milli-bitcoins) you would like to donate. One bitcoin is the same as 1000 mBTC. The current market rate in US dollars of your donation is shown. If you are not linked to a Coinbase account, your donation will be created as a pledge that you can fulfill once you have connected to a funded Coinbase account. If you are already connected to Coinbase, then your donation will be immediately funded from the bitcoin in your Coinbase account.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>
                        Fulfill Pledge
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="clearfix">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="sprite arrow"></div>
                    <h3>
                        Claim Campaign Funds
                    </h3>
                    <p>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
